comments: Booker's (PHX) arms are not vertical and he moves into Porzingis's (DAL) space and makes contact to his inner arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) makes contact with Finney-Smith's (DAL) wrist as they pursue the loose ball and contact affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Porzingis (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Paul's (PHX) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
During the drive, Ayton (PHX) makes contact to Doncic's (DAL) body and the contact affects his SQBR.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Ayton (PHX) grabs Richardson's (DAL) hip and dislodges him from his position in the lane.
Booker (PHX) and Richardson (DAL) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Richardson (DAL) makes incidental contact to Booker's (PHX) arm after the release of his driving shot attempt.
Porzingis (DAL) and Ayton (PHX) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Ayton (PHX) briefly places a hand on Doncic's (DAL) side and marginal contact occurs during his drive with 30.6 seconds remaining.
Porzingis (DAL) makes contact with the part of Ayton's (PHX) hand that is on the ball prior to it becoming dislodged as they pursue the loose ball.
Porzingis (DAL) hedges the pick and marginal contact occurs to Paul's (PHX) arm during his drive.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) makes contact to Ayton's (PHX) arm that affects his putback shot attempt.
Porzingis (DAL) clamps Ayton's (PHX) arm as the ball is released and contact affects his ability to get to the jump ball.
Richardson (DAL) and Booker (PHX) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Richardson (DAL) legally contests Booker (PHX) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Johnson (PHX) briefly places a hand on Doncic's (DAL) side and immediately removes it during the start of his upward shooting motion.
